or work against your interests.
Rebel groups allow you to engage in guerilla warfare in the province
this allows you to supply them a deck of military equipment and conduct 
operations to take control of the provinces infrastructure without declaring
war, a hybrid war allows for you to seize the province without

Aiding rebels helps bring them towards your control

A Province is divided into the following:
Human Security this metric is a abstraction of the provinces level of safety and danger, if a province has a
high level it is very safe, it is low then risk of daily deaths of civilians is likely
Rule of Law this metric is a abstraction of the unction of the state in the province and its ability to carry out policy
and enforce laws, the state becomes unable to control the population the rule of law lowers to a critical point 
where lawless occurs during this point the government of the local province is in anarchy and borders are fluid
you can move your forces in as peacekeepers or conquers depending on how you approached the situation.
Culture Value this metric is a abstraction of of the relevance of the province to the state, the more important the
province is to the state as a whole and its value to the world, controlling these provinces allows for soft power and 
increases in all a sectors and influence, it can be summed by the human desire to be in these province regardless
of the government in control.
Economic Activity this metric is a abstraction of the trade, business and industry, if a population is large and has
low activity the people will likely revolt, trade and increases in infrastructure and construction allow for economic 
activity to increase, corruptions and military conflict dramatic decrease economic activity.
Martial Law when martial law is declared the people have much less rights contacts can be jailed without repercussions
and the state will take over during a war.
State of Emergencies - this is a temporary measure when a natural disaster or military conflict occurs in a province but
doesn't directly trigger a war, a state of emergency is the same as martial law only can't last very long and doesn't suspend
jailing contacts without repercussions.

Freeze Assets - seizing the assets of this country will remove the money invested in the sectors, it is simlair to
economic sanctions as it effects sectors but takes away Hard currency from the country, unfreezing the assets
allows the hard currency back into the country.

Travel ban - enforcing a travel ban will block people coming and going from this country, the effect will be increase
in security and blocking intel actions and covert actions from a country, but at the cost of cultural value and economic 
activity

Inspections - Enabling inspections will trigger a host of trade barriers for the country and make it harder
to sell there products in your country, ,it will increase domestic production, but lower economic activity
, and increase province cultural value and rule of law

Dumping -  Preventing dumping from this country will raise domestic sector prices for your industries, it 
will lower relations will your country over time,

Subsidies - Using a subside will greatly increase the favorability of you in the country, but it will also lower
the income you make from your trade deals, subsides are per sector, 

Enforce Licenses - Enforcing the licenses is a way to lower economic activity but increase rule of law, 
the use of licenses allows for income to increase from trading deals with this country

Commercial Ban - 
Activating a Commercial Ban will lower the economic activity of the country if it is your on your border It will 
also lower the human security slightly the longer it goes on, and the increase the country imports from other
countries
